Lee Sang-yeob (born May 8, 1983) is a South Korean actor. He is best known for starring in the sitcom Living Among the Rich (2011â€“12), the melodrama  The Innocent Man (2012), the period drama Jang Ok-jung, Living by Love (2013), and the fantasy drama While You Were Sleeping (2017).
Lee was cast in his first leading role in the weekend drama A Little Love Never Hurts (2013). He recently gained immense recognition for portraying the role of Yoon Gyu-jin in the weekend drama Once Again (2020).

Personal life
Lee is the only grandson of the late businessman Kim Jong-jin, who served in executive positions at POSCO and Dongkuk Steel.

Relationship
On September 25, 2023, Lee's agency confirmed that Lee is getting married to his non-celebrity girlfriend in March 2024.

